[4] New Zealand (North Island)
Date: Thu 25 May 2017
Source: 1 News Now [edited]
https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/measles-case-confirmed-in-wellington-officials-warn-disease-could-spread-unless-people-get-checked


Measles case confirmed in Wellington as officials warn disease could spread unless people get checked.

Regional Public Health in Wellington has warned a single case of measles identified in the region could lead to more unless people get checked.

One person has come down with the disease and Medical Officer of Health Annette Nesdale says anyone who visited the locations [listed in the URL] at the relevant times, and is not immunized, should see their GP.

Ms Nesdale explained ..."We are contacting people who have been in contact with the unwell person because measles is an airborne disease anyone who was at the above listed locations at the times specified, should remain vigilant," she said.

