[There are currently 68 cases of measles reported in Minnesota, almost exclusively in Hennepin County. See ProMED-mail Measles update (27) http://promedmail.org/post/20170516.5039511 for earlier update on the outbreak in Minnesota prior to this jump to 68 cases. The cases are almost exclusively in U.S.-born children of Somali descent.

The Washington Post reported on 5 May that MMR vaccination rates among U.S.-born children of Somali descent used to be higher than among other children in Minnesota. But the rates plummeted from 92 percent in 2004 to 42 percent in 2014, state health department data shows, well below the threshold of 92 to 94 percent needed to protect a community against measles.

[It is concerning] that Wakefield, a British activist who now lives in Texas, visited Minneapolis at least 3 times in 2010 and 2011 to meet privately with Somali parents of autistic children, according to local anti-vaccine activists. Wakefield's prominence stems from a 1998 study he authored that claimed to show a link between the vaccine and autism. The study was later identified as fraudulent and was retracted by the medical journal that published it, and his medical license was revoked.

Read the full article from 5 May and see a figure of the plummeting vaccine rate in Minnesota (http://wapo.st/2r7JbZe).

The state of Minnesota can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5065373,354. A county map can be seen at http://geology.com/county-map/minnesota-county-map.gif. - Mod.LK]


